AN ACT relating to governmental administration; revising the
membership of the Nevada State Board on Geographic
Names; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law creates the Nevada State Board on Geographic Names to
2 coordinate and approve geographic names within the State for official
3 recommendation to the United States Board on Geographic Names. (NRS 327.110)
4 The Nevada State Board on Geographic Names consists of 12 voting members,
5 which include various representatives from various state and federal agencies and
6 the Inter-Tribal Council of Nevada, Inc. (NRS 327.120) Section 1 of this bill: (1)
7 removes the representative from the Nevada Historical Society on the Nevada State
8 Board on Geographic Names; (2) adds to the Board one representative from the
9 Division of Museums and History of the Department of Tourism and Cultural
10 Affairs; (3) clarifies that the representative from the Department of Native
11 American Affairs is from the Department of Native American Affairs of this State;
12 and (4) changes the representatives from the United States Bureau of Land
13 Management, the United States Forest Service and the United States National Park
14 Service from voting members of the Board to nonvoting members. Section 2 of this
15 bill allows the representative appointed by the Nevada Historical Society who is
16 serving on the Board on or before July 1, 2025, to continue serving on the Board
17 until the representative’s successor is designated by the appropriate agency in
18 accordance with the provisions of section 1.
